---
description: React/TypeScript conventions for the Blink web dashboard.
globs: ["blink-ui/src/**", "blink-engine/web-ui/src/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

## TypeScript
- Strict mode on. Never use `any` — use `unknown` + type guards.
- Prefer `type` over `interface`. Always type component props explicitly.

## React 19
- Use `use()` hook for async data, not `useEffect` + fetch.
- Derived state computed during render — not stored in `useState`.
- `useCallback`/`useMemo` only when profiling shows real cost.

## WebSocket
- Engine broadcasts every `WS_BROADCAST_INTERVAL_SECS` (default 10s).
- Handle `readyState` changes — show stale-data indicator when disconnected.
- Treat all incoming WS data as `readonly`.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS 4 utility classes only. No custom CSS files.
- Monetary values: `$X.XX` (2dp). Prices as decimals (`0.65`), not percentages.

## API
- Dashboard REST/WebSocket traffic is served by the engine on port `3030`; agent JSON-RPC is a separate surface on `7878`.
- Handle 503/network errors — engine may not be running.

## Quality
- `npm run lint` must pass. Never `// eslint-disable`.
- `npm run build` (tsc + vite) must succeed before committing.
